RALPH LEFT GRABERA IN
SEVEN THOUSAND THREE

160
00:09:29,041 --> 00:09:30,166
STANDARD ERA, RIGHT?

161
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,916
WHICH MEANS HE SHOULD
STILL BE TRAVELING

162
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,458
AT SUB-LIGHTSPEED NOW!

163
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:35,958
HE HASN'T EVEN CAUGHT UP TO
THE TARGET AUXILIARY VESSEL YET!

164
00:09:36,041 --> 00:09:37,291
- Carmichael: I GET IT.

165
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:39,291
- THAT'S RIGHT.

166
00:09:39,375 --> 00:09:40,666
RALPH ACTUALLY CAUGHT
UP WITH THE TARGET

167
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:43,166
IN SEVENTY-FIVE SIXTY-FOUR
STANDARD ERA.

168
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:46,083
- BUT IF THAT'S TRUE, THEN HOW
DID HE MANAGE TO SHOW UP HERE?

169
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:47,250
HE COULDN'T HAVE!

170
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:49,375
- YES, HE COULD,
BECAUSE THE LAST GIRL

171
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:53,291
MY BROTHER DEFEATED
OPENED A GATE.

172
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:54,708
- Carmichael: BUT I THOUGHT
THE GATES WERE FOR

173
00:09:54,791 --> 00:09:56,583
INSTANT TRANSPORTATION
THROUGH SPACE,

174
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:57,708
NOT TIME.

175
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:04,208
- Melchi: OF COURSE!

176
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:07,333
MULTIPLE TIMES EXIST WHEN
TRAVELING AT SUB-LIGHTSPEED!

177
00:10:07,416 --> 00:10:10,708
AND SHE CHOSE RALPH'S SUBJECTIVE
TIME OF SEVEN THOUSAND FIVE!

178
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,958
- SO, THAT WOULD MEAN
THE BAXTER GATE CONNECTED

179
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:19,875
WITH SPACE IN SEVEN
THOUSAND FIVE, RIGHT?

180
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:20,958
- YEAH.

181
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:26,375
- AND THAT'S HOW RALPH WEREC
WAS CAPABLE OF RETURNING HERE.

182
00:10:26,458 --> 00:10:29,416
- AMAZING. SIMPLY AMAZING.

183
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,125
- THIS IS ALMOST
IMPOSSIBLE TO BELIEVE.

184
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:34,833
- WHEN IT HAPPENED, THE SUM
OF ALL OF THE MEMORIES AND

185
00:10:34,916 --> 00:10:36,375
FEELINGS OF THE GIRLS.

186
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:39,833
THEY CAME, THEY FLOWED
STRAIGHT INTO MY BROTHER.

187
00:10:54,166 --> 00:10:57,375
- ( Ralph screaming )

188
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:07,250
- Sara: AND THAT'S WHY,
HE WILL COME WITHOUT FAIL.

189
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:21,750
- Medlock: FINAL DECELERATION
COMPLETE. TARGET CONFIRMED.

190
00:11:23,208 --> 00:11:26,625
AM I USELESS TO YOU NOW?
YOU WANT TO KILL ME?

191
00:11:26,708 --> 00:11:28,166
- ( beeping )

192
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,291
- HEY. I NEED TO GO
TO THE RESTROOM,

193
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:34,750
OR IS THAT TOO MUCH TO ASK?

194
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,375
DON'T TRUST ME?

195
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:52,000
( thinking ) WHAT COULD
THIS MAN BE THINKING?

196
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:54,208
IF I'D HAD ANY IDEA THIS
WAS GOING TO HAPPEN,

197
00:11:54,291 --> 00:11:55,416
I WOULDN'T HAVE...

198
00:11:59,875 --> 00:12:01,916
AN OLD MODEL UNION SHIP?

199
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:05,000
STRANGE, HOW DID IT COME
THIS FAR IN THAT CONDITION?

200
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:07,916
- WE HAVE VIDEO FOOTAGE FROM
A RECONNAISSANCE TUMOR UNIT.

201
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
- GOOD.

202
00:12:12,791 --> 00:12:13,916
- Barrow: A SURVIVOR?

203
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:16,791
- I WISH TO DEFECT.

204
00:12:16,875 --> 00:12:19,416
LET ME SPEAK WITH
YOUR COMMANDER.

205
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,250
I WISH TO DEFECT.
LET ME SPEAK.

206
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:26,125
I AM A REASONER OF
THE UNION, RALPH WEREC.

207
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:29,541
- Medlock: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

208
00:12:29,625 --> 00:12:31,166
- Barrow: I HAVE
A HARD TIME BELIEVING

209
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,208
INSTANT INTERSTELLAR
COMMUNICATION IS POSSIBLE,

210
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:36,375
BUT, THERE IS
A CHANCE IT'S REAL.

211
00:12:36,458 --> 00:12:38,250
IF IT'S WITHIN OUR
POWER TO OBTAIN IT,

212
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,833
I ADVISE WE GIVE IT A TRY.

213
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:40,958
- Medlock: INDEED.

214
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:42,416
- Barrow: IF WE
RETURNED HOME NOW,

215
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,083
WE WOULD HAVE THREE YEARS
UNTIL OUR NEXT OPERATION.

216
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:48,333
AND I DON'T DOUBT THEY WOULD
GIVE US A FULL VACATION.

217
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:49,458
- Medlock: SO YOU'RE SAYING
YOU WOULD RATHER

218
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:51,208
TAKE A SHOT AT GAINING GLORY?

219
00:12:51,291 --> 00:12:52,333
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

220
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,875
- YOU'RE IN NEED
OF ANOTHER ONE?

221
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:02,125
I THOUGHT YOU SAID THIS
ONE WOULD BE SUFFICIENT

